    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "equipment",
        "text": "Though it resembles an enormous leaf freshly plucked from a tree, a *broadleaf shield* is extremely durable. It also regrows rapidly, fully repairing itself when broken if it's left in sunlight for 10 consecutive minutes.  \n   \n At each dawn, the leaf transforms to an appearance appropriate for the season. While you're wielding the shield, you gain resistance to a damage type depending on the shield's color. This resistance doubles while you have the shield raised. \n* **Pink** (void resistance) In spring, the leaf is a delicate blossom-like pink and exudes the energy of life.\n* **Green** (fire resistance) In summer, the leaf is a deep, rich green with a waxy coating.\n* **Orange** (poison resistance) In autumn, the leaf turns orange, red, or yellow and dehydrates slightly.\n* **Brown** (cold resistance) In winter, the leaf turns dead, dry, and brown.",
        "level": 6,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Magical",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 103,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
                "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Plant",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 125,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 459",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 459,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "651e06f09e5aea780d7c70a36ce5b1f2",
                "text": "Vegetable creatures have the plant trait. They are distinct from normal plants. Magical effects with this trait manipulate or conjure plants or plant matter in some way. Effects that manipulate plants have no effect in an area with no plants.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Wood",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 463,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "7c548a9e0a2647c082989720b3de0a87",
                "text": "Effects with the wood trait conjure or manipulate wood. Those that manipulate wood have no effect in an area without wood. Creatures with this trait consist primarily of wood or have a connection to magical wood.  \n  \nThese planes consist of trees and other flora latticed in organic patterns. Wood planes are often perfectly constructed to match their desired purpose or environment but aren\u2019t usually outright hostile to visitors.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            }
        ],
